        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=5229&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=The+Fuhrer+speaks%2C+Heil+him%21%21"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>On June 4th, 2001, SOE banned and/or suspended 28 players belonging to the guild Conquest. Plainly put, they were cheating, we observed them cheating, they knew they were cheating, they admitted they were cheating, and they got caught. </P><P>While SOE does not want to spoil the game by releasing full details of the cheats to all players, basically the 28 Conquest players were (among other things) purposely using world geometry, aspects of the hate list, the "z" coordinate and its nullification of NPC's ability to summon, and multiple atmospheres (e.g. water/land) to arrange dragon-type encounters so they could attack without getting hit back for the vast majority of the time that it took to kill the monster. In short, what they did was carefully orchestrate 100,000+ hps encounters so that, for 75% or more of the time that it took to kill the encounter, the monster got beaten on and was not able to fight back. </P><P>In addition, SOE staff observed various members of the guild discussing the cheating -- these comments include: </P><P>"we're useing [sic] massive amounts of exploits and u send a gm down here?" <BR>"Any lead GM shows up, this show is over." <BR>"yeah, this is the most impressive Itz-guyversploit [sic] to date" <BR>"every guild exploits these" </P><P>The EverQuest Rules of Conduct state, among other things: </P><P>"You will not exploit any bug in EverQuest and you will not communicate the existence of any such exploitable bug (bugs that grant the user unnatural or unintended benefits in game), either directly or through public posting, to any other user of EverQuest. You will promptly report any such bug via the in-game "/bug" command or via the eqtesting@verant.com email address." </P><P>"Disciplinary issues involving guilds will also be addressed on a broader basis. Guilds whose members habitually violate any of the Rules of Conduct . . . may be disbanded." </P><P>As a result of this unfortunate incident, (i) most of the participants were suspended for one week, (ii) a few, who had received previous warnings or suspensions, were banned, and (iii) this guild has been disbanded. </P><P>SOE regrets having to take these measures, but SOE is committed to protecting the health and viability of the game and of the EverQuest community. We’d also like to correct a few related misconceptions regarding this event: (i) Conquest did not complete the encounter – SOE staff inadvertently spawned the Sleeper during it’s efforts to stop the cheating, (ii) the “human figures” in some screenshots are a result of the screenshot taker not patching, and (iii) the zone is complete and working -- once SOE has patched fixes to these exploits we encourage players to wake the Sleeper. </P><P>We appreciate everyone’s emails with regards to questions and we do hope this will assist everyone in an understanding of the situation. </P><P>-The EverQuest Customer Service Team<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote> </P><P><BR>Okay now that you're done laughing lemme translate this...</P><P>First off the comments are hillarious, as they are obviously sarcastic and/or are taken out of context to look incriminating. </P><P>Second, using <b>"world Geometry"</b> to gain an unfair advantage? Ok so i guess now all the geometry in the game is only for pretty look but dont touch. Don't run up hills, thats exploiting. Don't jump off ledges to avoid getting hit, thats an exploit. Don't do anything that doesnt result in you dying, thats an exploit. Oh ok then, so now the game is even more boring then ever, unless you and absor love dying, then this game roxx!! </P><P><b>"z" coordinate and its nullification of NPC's ability to summon</b>Hehe who's fault is that brad? Next time test the game, or hell even play it.</P><P><b>75% or more of the time that it took to kill the encounter, the monster got beaten on and was not able to fight back.</b></P><P>Jeeze that sounds exactly like fear kiting, is that why you've completely screwed over necros?</P><P>I'm sorry Brad, sounds to me like your wetdream of a mob got beaten, pathetically, and your gm's got hot tempered(what a shocker, they're usually so calm and professional) and now you guys gotta play cover-up and find an excuse. Heya this reminds me of that time you banned Mystere the roleplayer for making a story, of course you guys had to scramble to make up excuses and finally pinned her/him for using game content without your consent.</P><P>God you guys are pathetic, btw the game blows 50+, fix it before the next MMOG comes out, you stupid pricks.</P><P>The Creation of Potus<BR><img src="http://members.spree.com/sip1/farkenb/potadam.jpg"" border=0></font></td>
